---
import Base from "@layouts/Base.astro";
import Header from "@components/Header.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<Base
  title="Work with Berk Saraloglu | Senior Marketing Manager, Hamburg"
  description="11+ years building marketing infrastructure: scaled organic media value to €M+, 600% CRM growth, 117% launch targets. Seeking Senior Marketing Manager role in Hamburg or DACH."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">

    <section class="pt-16 pb-10 border-b border-gray-100">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-green-700 bg-green-100 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-green-500 rounded-full animate-pulse"></span>
          Available now
        </span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 leading-tight">
        Senior Marketing Manager<br />based in Hamburg
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        11+ years building marketing infrastructure that delivers. Organic media scaled to €M+. 600% CRM database growth. 117% launch targets. Led 20+ markets simultaneously at BSH. Built EU-wide IMC operating systems at VeSync. Now looking for a Senior Marketing Manager role in Hamburg or DACH—ideally at a company taking AI seriously.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- What I'm looking for -->
    <section class="py-12 border-b border-gray-100">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">What I'm looking for</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        {[
          { label: "Location", value: "Hamburg or DACH (no relocation)" },
          { label: "Role level", value: "Senior Marketing Manager or equivalent" },
          { label: "Start", value: "Available immediately" },
          { label: "Industry fit", value: "Consumer electronics, lifestyle, B2B SaaS, AI/tech" },
          { label: "Company stage", value: "Scale-up to enterprise, team of 5+ in marketing" },
        ].map(({ label, value }) => (
          <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-100">
            <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">{label}</div>
            <div class="font-medium text-gray-900">{value}</div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What I bring -->
    <section class="py-12 border-b border-gray-100">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What I bring</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Concrete patterns, not credentials. Here's what I'd actually do in the first 30 days.</p>
      <div class="mb-5 border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 rounded-xl p-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Where I want to take the function by 2027</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">A small marketing team should operate like an intelligence system: one clear revenue story, shared customer evidence, AI-assisted production, and weekly decisions grounded in what moved qualified demand. That is the function I want to build: faster than a traditional brand team, more disciplined than a content shop, and close enough to product to know what is actually true.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">I map the revenue story before touching a campaign</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">My first 30 days: audit what's actually driving revenue versus what the team thinks is driving it. At VeSync, I built 3 full-funnel playbooks from scratch using Jobs-to-Be-Done interviews. At BSH, I restructured content production to save €1.5M annually while lifting organic reach across 10+ countries. I don't optimise channels before I understand the underlying customer logic.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">See the full VeSync case study at <a href="/career/vesync" class="text-gray-900 underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-gray-700 transition-colors">/career/vesync</a> for the complete project breakdown.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">I run launches end-to-end, including the uncomfortable parts</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Ran the full-funnel launch of a premium airfryer at VeSync: 117% of sell-out target in 53 days across 8 channels simultaneously. That includes aligning category managers, briefing agencies, owning the budget, and delivering post-mortems without softening the numbers. I know what it takes to go from brief to shelf.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">See the full VeSync case study at <a href="/career/vesync" class="text-gray-900 underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-gray-700 transition-colors">/career/vesync</a> for the complete project breakdown.</p>
        </div>
        {[
          {
            title: "I manage cross-functional complexity without escalating everything",
            desc: "Led 15+ stakeholders across Germany and China HQ at VeSync without line authority. Aligned country teams across 10+ markets at Bosch Siemens Home Appliances (BSH). The skill isn't influence tactics. It's building shared governance: joint OKRs, clear decision rights, and communication rhythms that don't collapse under pressure.",
          },
          {
            title: "I use AI as infrastructure, not a content shortcut",
            desc: "I'm building vision-intelligence, an AI marketing platform for DACH SMEs. That means I understand the real implementation gap: most teams can generate content with AI but can't integrate it into their measurement stack or approval workflows. I close that gap. I can audit your current AI usage, identify three high-leverage automations, and have the first one running within the first month.",
          },
        ].map(({ title, desc }) => (
          <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-5">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">{title}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">{desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- A few honest answers -->
    <section class="py-12 border-b border-gray-100">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">A few honest answers</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6 max-w-2xl">
        Recruiters usually have these questions. Here are the direct answers.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        {[
          {
            q: "Why did you leave VeSync?",
            a: "Relocation requirement, not performance. VeSync centralised European operations to Amsterdam. My family base is in Hamburg and my wife's nursing certification process is tied to Germany until end of 2026. I could not relocate to Amsterdam. The role was good; the geography did not work.",
          },
          {
            q: "Why are you looking now?",
            a: "I left in May 2026 to search properly rather than rush into the wrong role. I have an 18-month runway. I am not applying out of financial pressure. I am looking for the right fit, which means a company where marketing has real budget authority and the leadership team takes product seriously.",
          },
          {
            q: "How long will you stay?",
            a: "I target 3 to 5 years in the right environment. My last two exits were structural, not motivational. I stay when I have scope, trust, and a team worth building with. I leave when the governance breaks down and I can see it will not recover.",
          },
        ].map(({ q, a }) => (
          <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-5">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">{q}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">{a}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Consulting -->
    <section class="py-12 border-b border-gray-100">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Also available for consulting</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6 max-w-2xl">
        While I look for the right permanent role, I take on selective consulting work in two areas:
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-5 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl">
          <div class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">AI marketing transformation</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Your team is using AI tools but the output is inconsistent and nothing connects to your reporting stack. I audit current usage, identify the three highest-leverage automations for your specific workflows, and implement the first one. Relevant for DACH companies that have moved beyond experimenting but have not yet systematised.</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">Read the full DACH SME marketing guide at <a href="/ai-marketing-dach" class="text-gray-900 underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-gray-700 transition-colors">/ai-marketing-dach</a> to understand the framework I'd apply to your business.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl">
          <div class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Product launch strategy</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">You have a product ready for DACH but no structured go-to-market plan. I build the brief, the channel mix, the sell-out target model, and the agency briefs. Engagement runs from kick-off through launch week. I have done this for premium hardware and can compress the planning cycle by 30–40%.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Get in touch -->
    <section class="py-12">
      <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl p-8 text-white">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Let's talk if this fits</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          If you are building a marketing function in DACH, launching a product in the German market, or running a team that needs to integrate AI into its actual workflows, I can help. Email me with what you are working on and what the gap is. I respond to specific enquiries within 48 hours.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4 text-sm">Direct email: <a href="mailto:berksaraloglu@gmail.com?subject=Senior%20Marketing%20role%20via%20saralogy.com" class="text-white underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-gray-200 transition-colors">berksaraloglu@gmail.com</a>. Or explore my full marketing background at <a href="/career" class="text-white underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-gray-200 transition-colors">/career</a> to see the pattern across roles.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a
            href="mailto:berksaraloglu@gmail.com?subject=Senior%20Marketing%20role%20via%20saralogy.com"
            class="bg-white text-gray-900 px-6 py-2.5 rounded-full font-medium text-sm hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors"
          >
            Email Berk →
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://linkedin.com/in/berksaraloglu"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="border border-gray-700 text-gray-300 px-6 py-2.5 rounded-full font-medium text-sm hover:border-gray-400 transition-colors"
          >
            Message on LinkedIn →
          </a>
          <a
            href="/about"
            class="border border-gray-700 text-gray-300 px-6 py-2.5 rounded-full font-medium text-sm hover:border-gray-400 transition-colors"
          >
            Full background →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <footer class="border-t border-gray-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 sm:items-center sm:justify-between text-sm text-gray-500">
      <span>© 2026 Berk Saraloglu · AI-native marketing leader in Hamburg</span>
      <div class="flex gap-6">
        <a href="/now" class="hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors">Now</a>
        <a href="mailto:berksaraloglu@gmail.com?subject=Opportunity%20via%20saralogy.com" class="hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors">Email</a>
        <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/berksaraloglu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors">LinkedIn</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/berksaraloglu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors">GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Base>
